I assisted two team members who were experiencing failures following our software upgrade from version 4 to version 5. After replicating the error in my own instance of version 5, I began investigating the IDE configuration. I discovered that IntelliJ was not recognizing the updated dependency structure and was inadvertently pulling legacy code from the version 5 build. To rectify this, I executed a full "Synch All Gradle Projects" via the Gradle tool window. This forced IntelliJ to re-index the project and correctly map the new version’s dependencies, which immediately cleared the errors and ensured the team was working with a consistent and functional build environment.
